<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-14T16:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-14T16:32:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/8–1452: Telegram</note>
                    <head>No. 200<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United
                                Kingdom</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d200fn1">Also sent to
                            Tehran. Drafted and signed by <persName corresp="#p_RAL1">Richards</persName>.</note></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-14T17:32:00-04:00">August 14, 1952—5:32
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1068. Fol <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> today handed to <persName corresp="#p_BBBA1">Burrows</persName> Brit Counselor: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“Instrs to <persName corresp="#p_MGH2">Middleton</persName> re
                                proposed reply to <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName> have
                                been carefully studied in Dept.</p>
                            <p>It is view of Dept that suggestion of informal conversations between
                                Reps of IranGov and of <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> has
                                merit and we wld be pleased if Dr. <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName> accepted this proposal.</p>
                            <p>Dept considers that alternate proposal, to be followed shld Dr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName> refuse suggestion
                                for informal conversations, wld be unacceptable to IranGov and wld
                                leave gen atmosphere worse rather than better. Reasons for this
                                belief were set forth in Secy’s msg to <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> of Aug 12 and need no elaboration
                            here.”</p></quote></p>
                    <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>